The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, October 14, 2003 				 AIDS grant from Gates
																								New Delhi, Oct. 13: The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation today released its first grant of $67.5 million for the prevention of HIV/AIDS in the two most HIV-endemic states of Andhra Pradesh and Karnataka, reports our special correspondent.																								Last year, Microsoft chief Bill Gates had come to India, interacted with non-government organisations working on HIV/AIDS and announced a grant of $100 million to contain the infection. Recently, it increased the amount to $200 million.																								The board of the Gates Foundation AIDS initiative in India had its first meeting today. It was attended by Tarun Das, director- general of the Confederation of Indian Industry, Azim Hasham Premji, chairperson, Wipro Corporation, Sudha Murty, Infosys Foundation trustee, Kapil Sibal, Congress MP, and cricketer Rahul Dravid. 
